import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['departure_delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['departure_delay'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['departure_delay'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['departure_delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["departure_delay"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(x=data['departure_delay'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["departure_delay"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Departure Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# read data
data = pd.read_json('flights-5k.json')

# convert time fields to datetime
data['air_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['air_time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
data = data[pd.notna(data['air_time'])]

# create scatter plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['air_time'], alpha=0.5)

# set chart title and axis labels
ax.set_title('What is the relationship between distance and flight time?')
ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
ax.set_ylabel('Air Time')

# add median line for air time
median_air_time = data['air_time'].median()
ax.axhline(median_air_time, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Air Time: {median_air_time}')

# add legend
ax.legend()

# show plot
plt.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('origin_airport').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin_airport'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin airport?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['counts'].max():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# read data
data = pd.read_json('flights-5k.json')

# convert date fields to date types
data['FL_DATE'] = pd.to_datetime(data['FL_DATE'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')

# drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['FL_DATE'])]

# create a new column to indicate cancelled flights
data['CANCELLED_FLIGHT'] = data['CANCELLED'].apply(lambda x: 'Cancelled' if x == 1 else 'Not Cancelled')

# group by cancelled flight status and count the number of flights
cancelled_flights = data.groupby('CANCELLED_FLIGHT').size().reset_index(name='COUNT')

# create a pie chart of cancelled vs. not cancelled flights
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.pie(cancelled_flights['COUNT'], labels=cancelled_flights['CANCELLED_FLIGHT'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
ax.axis('equal')

# set chart title
plt.title('What is the distribution of flight cancellations?', wrap=True)

# add legend
plt.legend(title='Flight Status', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))

# show plot
plt.show()
```
